Full Description: The KTrack founders, Owen Knott and Martin Knott, Jr. have extensive experience in facilities management and maintenance spanning from design and construction to building asset management. Currently, their firm Knott Mechanical is one Maryland’s premier commercial HVAC and plumbing service providers, working with more than 1,200 customers in Central Maryland providing service in over 2,000 buildings comprising 90 million sq. ft. of space. At its inception in 2002, the Founders chose to take a new approach to operating a mechanical services business. That tactic was to use technology to streamline the operations and provide clients real time advice and potential for solutions to problems that were encountered. To that end, the founders began work on what was to become KTrack.  Since 2003, Knott Mechanical has been using the KTrack platform to manage all aspects of asset management and maintenance for their clients. Using this robust software platform, Knott Mechanical has been able to realize a 120% increase in worker productivity and 200% increase in revenue per truck. Over the past three years, the KTrack founders have consciously evolved KTrack from a custom software product for internal use to a SaaS platform that serves as a bridge between the design, construction, operations and maintenance stages of construction and/or renovation of a facility. The Company has secured key customer wins in partnership with Whiting Turner: Maryland’s Wicomico County Public School District and Bexar County, Texas 911 Center. The leadership and execution skills of the management team are demonstrated by their accomplishments.

Full Description: OtherPage is a discount product aggregator that allows consumers to find merchants who usually sell on eBay or Amazon.com. OtherPage is integrated with ChannelAdvisor's SaaS ecommerce platform, so their 6,000 merchant customers can list their products easily on OtherPage. They also offer a revenue share business model, so that as opposed to paying in a cost-per-click model, the goals of OtherPage are alligned with their merchant partners: to drive additional order volume directly through the merchants existing ecommerce store. OtherPage announced in November that it would be launching a "social shopping" application that gives online shoppers cash back if their friends buy the same stuff. Users will get 1 to 5 percent cash rebates on purchases made via the site, which includes a price comparison tool and coupons. According to Brier Dudley of the Seattle Times, "sers will get 1 to 5 percent cash rebates on purchases made via the site, which includes a price comparison tool and coupons. They have the option of sharing their purchases and information about deals and stores on Facebook. If friends click through the shared information and make a purchase, the user will get an additional 1 to 5 percent back. OtherPage also provides icons that can be added to show "attitude and feeling" about products. The service is launching with about 500 participating stores, including Best Buy, Overstock and drugstore.com. It also provides about 10,000 coupons and price comparisons for about 5 million products."

Description: Sea Glass Mental Health is a woman-owned and solution-focused mental health practice that offers telehealth therapy services
Headquarters Regions: Greater Phoenix Area, Western US
Full Description: Sea glass is a symbol of renewal and healing. Starting as an intact object, it then endures the trauma of being broken. Each piece then tumbles through the waves and, with time, the jagged sides become smooth and the glass transforms into a treasure.  We understand that you may be feeling broken right now. Much like the journey of sea glass, you too may be feeling lost at sea as you struggle with the trials and tribulations of the human experience. We are here to help you navigate through this difficult time in your life. You are not alone. Sea Glass Mental Health is a woman-owned and solution-focused practice that is committed to helping our clients become the best and healthiest versions of themselves.  We work with individuals and couples from all walks of life, utilize modern evidence-based practices and provide practical tools to achieve sustainable results. Our experienced and knowledgeable licensed therapists believe in an integrated, collaborative and individualized treatment model.  We understand that mental health is not a “one size fits all” approach.  We currently offer individual and couples Telehealth counseling services primarily to Arizona residents who are ages 15+. Our licensed therapists work with a wide variety of issues/topics/ populations including, but not limited to: depression, anxiety, PTSD, OCD, ASD, grief, ADHD, self-esteem, acute, complex and chronic trauma, relationship issues, stress, behavioral issues, addiction, family conflict, LGBTQIA+ issues, unhealthy relationships with food, mood disorders, personality disorders, sleep issues, parenting, divorce, spirituality, attachment, and more. If you are unsure about which therapist would be the best fit for you, please contact the Sea Glass Mental Health Support team for assistance.
